Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Developer position with Intelex Technologies. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web application development, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade full stack systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and developed full stack web application features across 1,000+ platform endpoints using object-oriented programming, translating customer requirements into scalable, high-performing software with rigorous API contract design and input validation. To keep these systems production-ready, I delivered a robust observability layer using LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks within agile sprint commitments, collaborating with cross-functional teams to enable troubleshooting and track quality metrics — reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through proactive analysis and continuous deployment practices. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to large scale web applications that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs — giving me direct, hands-on experience with cloud-native, multi-environment backend design. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications within an agile Scrum practice, collaborating with cross-functional teams including QA and Product Management. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to Intelex's core engineering responsibilities and drive impact within an agile engineering team practicing continuous improvement.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical communication and collaborative software development — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I led workshops on GPU programming and building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the excellent written and oral communication skills central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to Intelex's mission.

I have always been passionate about workplace safety and environmental sustainability, and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of Intelex's mission to enable organizations to save lives, improve the environment, and boost bottom lines. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

